---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="About me and what I do." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>About Me</h1>
			<p>Hi, I'm Kaighn Kevlin.</p>
			<p>
				I'm a Software Engineer at Google living in a 5th-floor walk-up in the West Village, NYC.
				Day-to-day, I spend my time working on large-scale architecture and distributed systems.
				Off the clock, I'm usually deep in a Chrome tab, letting Claude Code help me build out
				whatever side project has my attention that week.
			</p>
			<p>
				This site is my digital garden. It's where I host interactive web widgets (like my
				housing simulator), experiment with AI agents (like Kaighnbot), and document my long-term
				project: an indie game built in Godot that blends Terraria, Factorio, and tower defense
				mechanics.
			</p>

			<h2>Out of Office</h2>
			<p>When I step away from the keyboard, I am usually:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>On the Mountain:</strong> Maximizing my Epic Pass. You will find me at Whistler (the clear winner over Breckenridge for elevation and crowds).</li>
				<li><strong>Watching Duke:</strong> Closely following both the men's and women's basketball teams.</li>
				<li><strong>Playing Games:</strong> Either digital (roguelikes, simulation, and strategy) or tabletop (mostly Root and chess).</li>
				<li><strong>Hanging with the Cats:</strong> I have two, including Gracie, who is the undisputed boss of the apartment.</li>
				<li><strong>Exploring NYC & Beyond:</strong> Whether it is trying out new recipes from local cooking boot camps, hitting up restaurants like WILD and Risotteria Melotti, or playing in a local kickball league.</li>
			</ul>

			<hr />
			<p><em>Disclaimer: All views, opinions, and projects shared on this site are my own and do not reflect the views or opinions of my employer.</em></p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
